headline: T-Mobile Visa Card Partnership Could Be a Game Changer for Capital One Financial (COF)
summary: Earlier this month, T-Mobile and Capital One introduced the T-Mobile Visa credit card, offering rewards linked to T-Mobile purchases and seamless digital features, with applications available online and at retail locations from November 10, 2025. This collaboration expands Capital One's access to T-Mobile’s broad customer base, potentially increasing its fee and interest income through integrated credit offerings and innovative digital rewards. headline: Buying an Older Used Car? You Might Be Surprised Which Lenders Will Finance It
summary: If you're buying a used car, Bank of America, Chase, First Tech FCU, and PNC Bank finance used vehicles, but have mileage and age restrictions for certain vehicles.

headline: Capital One Debit-Card Users Aren’t All Happy After the Switch to Discover
summary: The bank is moving its debit cards over from the Mastercard network after completing its acquisition of Discover earlier this year.
